d commuting system linking the high-priced and crowded Bay Area with the low-priced and low-density Central Valley. This would dramatically reduce travel times. And based on the operating speeds of hovering trains used in countries such as Japan or Spain, high-speed rail could shorten the time to travel between San Francisco and California\'s capital, Sacramento, or from Stockton to San Jose, to under 30 minutes. This system would bring once distant regions within reasonable commute to heavy job centers. The city also needs to update existing transportation routes combined with smart home-building policies that dramatically increase housing density in areas surrounding high-speed rail stations. By doing so, we will be able to build affordable housing within acceptable commuting distances for a significant bulk of the workforce.\"}, {\"key\": \"L\", \"value\": \"Our threatening housing crisis forces the difficult question of what type of society we would like to be. Will it be one where the elite command the vast bulk of wealth and regional culture is defined by an aggressive business world? We were recently treated to a taste of the latter, when local tech employee Justin Keller wrote an open letter to the city complaining about having to see homeless people on his way to work.\"}, {\"key\": \"M\", \"value\": \"It doesn\'t have to be this way. But solutions need to be implemented now, before angry crowds grow from a nuisance to serious concern. It may take less than you might think. And in fact, the solutions to our housing crisis are already fairly clear. We need to increase the density of housing units. We need to use existing technology to shorten travel times and break the land limits. There is a way to solve complex social and economic problems without abandoning social responsibility. This is the Bay Area\'s opportunity to prove that it can innovate more than just technology.\"}]', '[\"K\"]', '细节推断题。K)段第一句指出,仅靠房地产并不能解决问题。由上一段可知,该句中的 the problem 是指 the housing crisis。紧接着该段第二句提出其他的解决方法:更新交通,扩展基础设施,以便将遥远地区与硅谷和旧金山市连接起来。由此可以推知,将遥远地区与城市连接起来的交通和基础设施有助于解决住房危机。题干中的 improved transport networks 对应原文中的 transportation, too, needs to be updated,题干中的 connecting the city to distant outlying areas 是对原文中 link distant regions to Silicon Valley and the city 的同义转述,故答案为K)。', 1.0, 44);
INSERT INTO `question_sub_items` VALUES (111, 22, 'Average incomes in the Bay Area make it virtually impossible for most tenant families to buy a home.', 'choice', '[{\"key\": \"A\", \"value\": \"The fog still chills the morning air and the cable cars still climb halfway to the stars. Yet on the ground, the Bay Area has changed greatly since singer Tony Bennet left his heart here. Silicon Valley and the tech industry have led the region into a period of unprecedented wealth and innovation. But existing political and land limits have caused an alarming housing crisis and astronomical rise in social and economic difference.\"}, {\"key\": \"B\", \"value\": \"While the residents of most cities display pride and support for their home industries, drastic market distortions in the San Francisco Bay Area have created boiling resentment in the region towards the tech industry. A vocal minority is even calling on officials to punish those who are benefitting from the economic and housing boom. If this boom and its consequences are not resolved, a drastic increase in social and economic difference may have a profound impact on the region for generations. A history and analysis of this transformation may hold invaluable insights about the opportunities. Perils of tech cities are currently being cultivated across the US, and indeed around the world.\"}, {\"key\": \"C\", \"value\": \"According to a recent study, San Francisco ranks first in California for economic difference. The average income of the top 1% of households in the city averages $3.6 million. This is 44 times the average income of those at the bottom, which stands at $81,094. The top 1% of the San Francisco peninsula\'s share of total income now extends to 30.8% of the region\'s income. This was a dramatic jump from 1989, where it stood at 15.8%.\"}, {\"key\": \"D\", \"value\": \"The region\'s economy has been fundamentally transformed by the technology industry springing from Silicon Valley. Policies pushed by Mayor Ed Lee provided tax breaks for tech companies to set up shop along the city\'s long-neglected Mid-Market area. The city is now home to Twitter, Uber, Airbnb, Pinterest, Dropbox and others. In short, the Bay Area has become a global magnet for those with specialized skills, which has in turn helped fuel economic enthusiasm, and this economic growth has reduced unemployment to 3.4%, an admirable feat.\"}, {\"key\": \"E\", \"value\": \"In spite of all that, the strength of the recent job growth, combined with policies that have traditionally limited housing development in the city and throughout the peninsula, did not help ease the affordability crisis. In 2015 alone, the Bay Area added 64,000 in jobs. In the same year, only 5,000 new homes were built.\"}, {\"key\": \"F\", \"value\": \"With the average house in the city costing over $1. 25 million and average flat prices over $1.11million, the minimum qualifying income to purchase a house has increased to $254,000. Considering that the average household income in the city currently stands at around $ 80, 000, it is not an exaggeration to say that the dream of home ownership is now beyond the grasp of the vast majority of today\'s people who rent.\"}, {\"key\": \"G\", \"value\": \"For generations, the stability and prosperity of the American middle class has been anchored by home ownership. Studies have consistently shown that the value of land has overtaken overall income growth, thus providing a huge advantage to property owners as a vehicle of wealth building. When home prices soar above the reach of most households, the gap between the rich and the poor dramatically increases.\"}, {\"key\": \"H\", \"value\": \"If contributing factors leading to housing becoming less than affordable are not resolved over multiple generations, a small elite will control a vast share of the country\'s total wealth. The result? A society where the threat of class warfare would loom large. A society\'s level of happiness is tied less to measures of quantitative wealth and more to measures of qualitative wealth. This means that how a person judges their security in comparison to their neighbors\' has more of an impact on their happiness than their objective standard of living. At the same time, when a system no longer provides opportunities for the majority to participate in wealth building, it not only robs those who are excluded from opportunities, but also deprives them of their dignity.\"}, {\"key\": \"I\", \"value\": \"San Francisco and the Bay Area have long been committed to values which embrace inclusion and rejection of mainstream culture. To see these values coming apart so publicly adds insult to injury for a region once defined by its progressive social fabric. In the face of resentment, it is human to want revenge. But deteriorating policies such as heavily taxing technology companies or real estate developers are not likely to shift the balance.\"}, {\"key\": \"J\", \"value\": \"The housing crisis is caused by two primary factors: the growing desirability of the Bay Area as a place to live due to its excellent economy, and our limited housing stock. Although the city is experiencing an unprecedented boom in new housing, more units are sorely needed. Protection policies were originally designed to suppress bad development and boost historic preservation in our urban areas. Now, too many developers are experiencing excessive delays. Meanwhile, there are the land limitations of the Bay Area to consider. The region is surrounded by water and mountains. Local governments need to aid development as well. This means increasing housing density throughout the region and building upwards while streamlining the approval process.\"}, {\"key\": \"K\", \"value\": \"Real estate alone will not solve the problem, of course. Transportation, too, needs to be updated and infrastructure extended to link distant regions to Silicon Valley and the city. We need to build an effective high-speed commuting system linking the high-priced and crowded Bay Area with the low-priced and low-density Central Valley. This would dramatically reduce travel times. And based on the operating speeds of hovering trains used in countries such as Japan or Spain, high-speed rail could shorten the time to travel between San Francisco and California\'s capital, Sacramento, or from Stockton to San Jose, to under 30 minutes. This system would bring once distant regions within reasonable commute to heavy job centers. The city also needs to update existing transportation routes combined with smart home-building policies that dramatically increase housing density in areas surrounding high-speed rail stations. By doing so, we will be able to build affordable housing within acceptable commuting distances for a significant bulk of the workforce.\"}, {\"key\": \"L\", \"value\": \"Our threatening housing crisis forces the difficult question of what type of society we would like to be. Will it be one where the elite command the vast bulk of wealth and regional culture is defined by an aggressive business world? We were recently treated to a taste of the latter, when local tech employee Justin Keller wrote an open letter to the city complaining about having to see homeless people on his way to work.\"}, {\"key\": \"M\", \"value\": \"It doesn\'t have to be this way. But solutions need to be implemented now, before angry crowds grow from a nuisance to serious concern. It may take less than you might think. And in fact, the solutions to our housing crisis are already fairly clear. We need to increase the density of housing units. We need to use existing technology to shorten travel times and break the land limits. There is a way to solve complex social and economic problems without abandoning social responsibility. This is the Bay Area\'s opportunity to prove that it can innovate more than just technology.\"}]', '[\"F\"]', '细节推断题。F)段最后一句指出,考虑到该市平均家庭收入目前约为8万美元,毫不夸张地说,拥有住房的梦想是如今绝大多数租房者力所不能及的。由此可以推知,旧金山湾区的平均家庭收入太低,使绝大多数租房家庭几乎不可能买房。题干中的average incomes in the Bay Area 和“virtually impossible. . . to buy a home”对应原文中的 the average household income in the city 和 the dream of home ownership is now beyond the grasp,题干中的 most tenant families 是对原文中 the vast majority of today\'s people who rent 的同义转述,故答案为F)。', 1.0, 45);
INSERT INTO `question_sub_items` VALUES (112, 23, 'In what way were humans thought to be unique?', 'choice', '[{\"key\": \"A\", \"value\": \"Being a major source of animal intelligence.\"}, {\"key\": \"B\", \"value\": \"Being the cornerstone of the creative world.\"}, {\"key\": \"C\", \"value\": \"Being capable of same-different discrimination.\"}, {\"key\": \"D\", \"value\": \"Being able to distinguish abstract from concrete.\"}]', '[\"C\"]', '事实细节题。定位句指出,根据相同点和不同点进行推论的能力曾被认为是人类所独有的。由此可知,人类曾被认为独一无二的能力就是区分异同点的能力,故答案为C)。【避错】定位句虽然提到了 intelligent thought,但并未提及人类与动物智力之间的关系,故排除A)项;B)项和D)项是分别利用定位句后半部分中的 cornerstone 和 abstract 设置的干扰,但原文并未提及创意世界,也未提及区分抽象与具体,故均排除。', 1.0, 46);
INSERT INTO `question_sub_items` VALUES (113, 23, 'What do we learn from the study published in Science?', 'choice', '[{\"key\": \"A\", \"value\": \"Our understanding of the bird world was biased.\"}, {\"key\": \"B\", \"value\": \"Our conception of birds\' intelligence was wrong.\"}, {\"key\": \"C\", \"value\": \"Our communication with birds was far from adequate.\"}, {\"key\": \"D\", \"value\": \"Our knowledge about bird psychology needs updating.\"}]', '[\"B\"]', '推理判断题。定位句引用研究评论者的话,指出发表于《科学》杂志上的研究挑战了我们对鸟脑的认知,而第三段首句也说明所谓对鸟脑的认知,是指对鸟类聪明程度的理解。综合可知,我们对鸟类智力(聪明程度)的理解是错误的,B)项的表述符合原文,故为答案。【避错】A)项表述过于笼统,没有说明鸟类世界的哪个具体方面,故排除;第三段中提到人类应与鸟类“交谈”,其实是设法去了解它们的聪明程度,并非真正的交流,故排除C)项;定位部分引用的是一位心理学家的观点,但其谈论的是鸟类的智力,而非鸟类心理学,故排除D)项。', 1.0, 47);
INSERT INTO `question_sub_items` VALUES (114, 23, 'What did the researchers discover about most ducklings from their experiment?', 'choice', '[{\"key\": \"A\", \"value\": \"They could associate shape with color.\"}, {\"key\": \"B\", \"value\": \"They reacted quickly to moving objects.\"}, {\"key\": \"C\", \"value\": \"They preferred colored objects to colorless ones.\"}, {\"key\": \"D\", \"value\": \"They could tell whether the objects were the same.\"}]', '[\"D\"]', '事实细节题。第六段开头提示本段介绍研究发现。由本段可知,小鸭子如果先看见过在某方面具有相同特点的一对物体,在第二次进行选择时,也会选择在这方面具有相同特点的一对物体,而不会选择不同的物体,可知它们能够分辨异同,这也符合第一段第二句提到的研究主题,故答案为D)。【避错】A)项干扰性较强,但根据原文第五段和第七段可知,小鸭子是要分辨在物体这些方面的异同点,而不是要将这两方面联系起来,故排除;原文没有提及鸭子对移动物体反应的快慢,故排除B)项;根据第六段,小鸭子是分辨不同的颜色,而非区分有色和无色,故排除C)项。', 1.0, 48);
INSERT INTO `question_sub_items` VALUES (115, 23, 'What was novel about the experiment in the study reported in Science?', 'choice', '[{\"key\": \"A\", \"value\": \"The animals used received no training.\"}, {\"key\": \"B\", \"value\": \"It used a number of colors and shapes.\"}, {\"key\": \"C\", \"value\": \"It was conducted by experimental psychologists.\"}, {\"key\": \"D\", \"value\": \"The ducklings were compared with other animals.\"}]', '[\"A\"]', '事实细节题。第九段首句指出,研究作者们首次证明,动物可以在未经训练的情况下学习概念之间的关系,而随后的第十段也提到,以往的研究所使用的动物都是经过全面的训练的,可知本项研究的新颖之处在于实验动物是未经训练的,故答案为A)。【避错】前文虽然提到了实验物体的颜色和形状,但并未说这是以往研究未曾用过的,故排除 B)项;文章引用观点时提到了实验心理学家,但并未明确说这项实验是由实验心理学家实施的,而且也不是这项实验的新颖之处,故排除C)项;第九段和第十段对比了本项研究与以往研究的不同,但本项研究只使用了鸭子作为实验对象,并未将其与其他动物对比,故排除D)。', 1.0, 49);
INSERT INTO `question_sub_items` VALUES (116, 23, 'What do we learn from Dr. Wasserman\'s comment on the study of animal minds at the end of the passage?', 'choice', '[{\"key\": \"A\", \"value\": \"It is getting more and more intricate.\"}, {\"key\": \"B\", \"value\": \"Research methods are being updated.\"}, {\"key\": \"C\", \"value\": \"It is attracting more public attention.\"}, {\"key\": \"D\", \"value\": \"Remarkable progress is being made.\"}]', '[\"D\"]', '推理判断题。定位句提到,沃瑟曼博士指出,在理解其他动物心智的能力方面,我们正处于一个革命性的阶段。由此可知,他认为研究者在针对动物的心智研究方面有了重大进展和突破,故答案为D)。【避错】在最后一段中,沃瑟曼博士只提到研究加深了我们对动物智力的理解,并强调我们在研究动物心智方面的进步,并未提及研究的复杂程度、研究方法,也未提到公众是否关注这样的研究,故排除其余三项。', 1.0, 50);
INSERT INTO `question_sub_items` VALUES (117, 23, 'What has been a standard piece of dietary advice for decades?', 'choice', '[{\"key\": \"A\", \"value\": \"People should cultivate a healthy eating habit.\"}, {\"key\": \"B\", \"value\": \"People should have a well-balanced diet.\"}, {\"key\": \"C\", \"value\": \"People should diversify what they eat.\"}, {\"key\": \"D\", \"value\": \"People should limit calorie intake to avoid obesity.\"}]', '[\"C\"]', '事实细节题。文章首段第一句指出,人们应尽量吃各种食物,增加饮食多样性,这是几十年 来,美国及世界各地对于公共卫生的一项基本建议。C)项意思与此一致,故为答案。原文中 dietary diversity 意思是“饮食多样性”,C)项中的 diversify what they eat 为该短义的同义替换。【避错】本文提到了健康饮食习惯的重要性,但没有说这是基本建议之一,A)项为过度推理,故排除;文章没有提到“均衡饮食”,也没有表明这是基本建议之一,B)项为无中生有,故排除;虽然文章第一段提到了肥胖问题,但没有说限制卡路里摄入是基本建议之一,故排除D)项。', 1.0, 51);
INSERT INTO `question_sub_items` VALUES (118, 23, 'What did the new research by the American Heart Association find?', 'choice', '[{\"key\": \"A\", \"value\": \"People seeking dietary diversity tend to eat more.\"}, {\"key\": \"B\", \"value\": \"Big eaters are more likely to become overweight.\"}, {\"key\": \"C\", \"value\": \"Dietary diversity is positively related to good health.\"}, {\"key\": \"D\", \"value\": \"Unhealthy food makes people gain weight more easily.\"}]', '[\"A\"]', '推理判断题。文章第一段第四句提到了美国心脏协会进行的一项新研究,第五句进一步指出,研究人员回顾了所有已发表的与饮食多样性相关的证据,发现饮食多样性与更多健康和不健康食物的摄入量都有相关性。由此可知,追求多样化的饮食可能导致人们吃得更多,故答案为A)项。【避错】第一段第四、五句表明了饮食多样性与吃更多食物之间的关系,即吃的种类多,可能会导致吃的量也增加,而非吃得多与体重之间的关系,B)项与原文意思不符,故排除;文章定位句提到了多样化饮食与身体健康的关系,由首段最后一句可知,这会导致肥胖问题,两者并非正相关,故排除C)项;由文章首段第五、六句可知,饮食多样性导致食物摄入量增加,进而导致肥胖,可知健康食物也会导致肥胖,并非只有不健康的食物使人更容易增重,D)项为过度推理,故排除D)项。', 1.0, 52);
INSERT INTO `question_sub_items` VALUES (119, 23, 'What could help to explain the contradiction between the new findings and the common public health.\nrecommendation?', 'choice', '[{\"key\": \"A\", \"value\": \"Most dietary guidelines around the world contradict one another.\"}, {\"key\": \"B\", \"value\": \"Conventional wisdom about diet is seldom supported by science.\"}, {\"key\": \"C\", \"value\": \"The methods researchers use to measure nutrition vary greatly.\"}, {\"key\": \"D\", \"value\": \"There is little consensus on the definition of dietary diversity.\"}]', '[\"D\"]', '推理判断题。文章第二段第一、二句指出,新研究的结果与标准饮食建议相矛盾,可能是因为对“饮食多样性”没有明确一致的定义。第三句进一步解释了专家用不同的方法来衡量饮食多样性。由此可知,新发现与一般公共卫生建议相矛盾是因为对饮食多样性的定义几乎没有共识,故答案为D)。【避错】文章没有提到世界上的饮食指南相互矛盾,只是在第一段第一句指出不同国家几十年来都建议多样化饮食,A)项为无中生有,故排除;本文并未提及关于饮食的传统智慧,且第二段第二句提到的是标准饮食建议似乎缺乏科学支持,与饮食的传统智慧无关,B)项张冠李戴,故排除;文章第二段最后一句提到了专家用不同的方法来衡量饮食多样性,而非衡量营养,C)项与原文不符,故排除。', 1.0, 53);
INSERT INTO `question_sub_items` VALUES (120, 23, 'What did Dr. Rao find after 20 years of research on obesity?', 'choice', '[{\"key\": \"A\", \"value\": \"Dietary diversity promotes healthy body weight.\"}, {\"key\": \"B\", \"value\": \"Eating patterns and weight gain go hand in hand.\"}, {\"key\": \"C\", \"value\": \"Diversified food intake may not contribute to health.\"}, {\"key\": \"D\", \"value\": \"There is no clear definition of optimal eating patterns.\"}]', '[\"C\"]', '推理判断题。文章第三段第二句提到,该研究的一位作者饶博士指出,他在肥胖领域研究了20年后发现,具有严格的生活方式和饮食的人通常比吃各种食物的人更瘦、更健康。随后一句进一步指出,有限的证据表明,摄入各种食物实际上与摄入更多的卡路里以及不良饮食模式和体重增加都有关。由此可知,多样化的食物摄入可能不利于健康,故答案为C)。【避错】第三段第三句指出,摄入各种食物实际上与摄入更多的卡路里以及不良饮食模式和体重增加都有关,而非饮食多样性促进健康体重,A)项表述与原文矛盾,故排除;第三段第三句提到了饮食多样性与不良饮食模式和体重增加之间的关系,但由此并不能推导出饮食模式和体重增加密切相关,故排除B)项;第三段第三句中提到了 optimal eating patterns,但指的是 dietary diversity(饮食多样性)与其之间的关系,另由原文第二段第二句可知,没有明确定义的是 dietary diversity(饮食多样性),而非 optimal eating patterns(最佳饮食模式),D)项与原文意思不符,故排除。', 1.0, 54);
INSERT INTO `question_sub_items` VALUES (121, 23, 'What does the passage say about people who eat a great variety of food?', 'choice', '[{\"key\": \"A\", \"value\": \"They tend to consume more sweets, sugar and red meat.\"}, {\"key\": \"B\", \"value\": \"They don\'t feel they have had enough until they overeat.\"}, {\"key\": \"C\", \"value\": \"They don\'t have any problems getting sufficient nutrition.\"}, {\"key\": \"D\", \"value\": \"They are more likely to eat foods beneficial to their health.\"}]', '[\"B\"]', '推理判断题。第三段最后一句指出,有些证据表明,一餐中可选择的食物种类更多,可能会延迟人们的饱腹感,实际上会增加人们的摄入量。由此可知,吃各种各样食物的人在感觉饱腹之前往往吃得过多。B)项意思与此一致,故为答案。【避错】文章最后一段提到了多样化饮食与吃甜食、红肉等有害食物的相关建议,但与本题无关,故排除A)项;文章没有提到吃各种各样食物的人是否摄入足够的营养,C)项为无中生有,故排除;文章没有提及吃各种各样食物的人更有可能吃有益于健康的食物,D)项为无中生有,故排除。', 1.0, 55);
INSERT INTO `question_sub_items` VALUES (122, 24, '请在下方作答 / Please write your answer below:', 'essay', NULL, '[\"Zhang Qian was China\'s first great explorer. He fearlessly overcame numerous challenges and embarked on two expeditions to the Western Regions. Zhang Qian established trade relations between China, West Asia and Europe and facilitated the transportation of Chinese silk and silk fabrics to these regions, thus opening up the famous \\\"Silk Road” in history. At the same time, he also introduced the customs, geographic culture and unique species of the Western Regions to the Central Plains, greatly broadening people\'s horizons. As historians pointed out, without Zhang Qian\'s missions to the Western Regions, the opening of the Silk Road and cultural exchanges between the Han Dynasty and the Western Regions or Europe would have been impossible.\"]', NULL, 1.0, 1);
INSERT INTO `question_sub_items` VALUES (123, 27, '请在下方作答 / Please write your answer below:', 'essay', NULL, '[\"The Challenges in Making a Decision\\nPeople are now increasingly aware of the challenges in making a decision when faced with too many\\nchoices. For us, having more choices may seem like a good thing, but it can actually lead to decision-making\\nchallenges.\\nOne of the main challenges of having too many choices is decision paralysis. When faced with a vast array\\nof options, we may feel overwhelmed and unsure of which choice to make. We may spend hours or even days\\nresearching, comparing and analyzing our options, which can lead to decision fatigue and loss of confidence in\\nour choices. Another challenge is the fear of missing out. We may feel like we need to explore every possible\\noption before making a decision, which may cause confusion even stress.\\nIn conclusion, having too many choices is a great challenge in decision-making. To overcome these\\nchallenges, it\'s important to recognize that no choice is perfect and that we should aim for good enough rather\\nthan perfection. It\'s essential to simplify our options and prioritize our values. We can do this by setting clear\\ngoals, eliminating non-essential choices, and seeking advice from trusted sources.\"]', '', 1.0, 1);
INSERT INTO `question_sub_items` VALUES (124, 28, '请在下方作答 / Please write your answer below:', 'essay', NULL, '[\"Zheng He is the most outstanding navigator in Chinese history, showcasing extraordinary wisdom and\\nexceptional talent in many fields such as navigation, diplomacy and military affairs. He led a massive fleet on\\nseven voyages to visit many countries and regions in the western Pacific and Indian Oceans, deepening mutual\\nunderstanding between China and Southeast Asia and East Africa.\\nZheng He\'s voyages to the West not only facilitated extensive economic and cultural exchanges between\\nChina and other nations but also made great contributions to maintaining regional peace. To commemorate\\nZheng He and his remarkable achievements, July 11, the day when he embarked on his first expedition with a\\nlarge fleet, has been designated as China\'s Maritime Day.\"]', '', 1.0, 1);
INSERT INTO `question_sub_items` VALUES (125, 29, '请在下方作答 / Please write your answer below:', 'essay', NULL, '[\"The Digital Gap the Elderly Face\\nPeople are now increasingly aware of the \\\"digital gap” or challenges the elderly face in a digital world. As technology advances, the gap between generations in terms of digital proficiency widens, making it difficult for many older adults to keep up.\\nOne significant challenge for older adults is access to technology. Many old people lack access to electronic devices such as smartphones or high-speed Internet, which may limit their ability to connect with loved ones, access healthcare services and stay informed about current events. Moreover, the elderly may also struggle with digital literacy, making it difficult to navigate the digital world. This can lead to social isolation and decreased engagement with society as many activities and services move online.\\nIn conclusion, the digital gap is a great challenge for the elderly. To address these challenges, it\'s essential to provide older adults with access to technology and resources that can help them navigate the digital world. This includes providing training and support, designing products with older adults in mind, and offering affordable Internet options. By bridging the gap, we can ensure that older adults can fully participate in the digital world.\"]', '', 1.0, 1);
INSERT INTO `question_sub_items` VALUES (126, 30, '请在下方作答 / Please write your answer below:', 'essay', NULL, '[\"Xu Xiake was a famous geographer in the Ming Dynasty of China. He spent over 30 years traveling throughout most of China, mainly on foot, and exploring many remote and desolate areas. He recorded his observations and research results in great detail, leaving valuable investigation materials for future generations. Through field investigations of many rivers, he corrected errors about their sources in the literature. In addition, he meticulously documented how topography, climate and other factors influenced plant growth, and vividly depicted the places of interest and local customs. His exploration records were compiled into the book Xu Xiake\'s Travels by later generations, which had a profound influence at home and abroad.\"]', '', 1.0, 1);
